North Korea said it welcomed newcontacts between Korean and U.S. Diplomats and would impose norestrictions on them, the New China News Agency reported fromPyongyang.    A North Korean Foreign Ministry statement said it hopeddiplomatic contact would help "promote sincere conversationswith goodwill and broad-mindedness," the agency said.    The United States on March 9 lifted its ban on itsdiplomats speaking with North Korean diplomats on neutralterritory. REUTER&#3;